result.formatted_address: Shum Wan Pier Dr, Aberdeen, Hong Kong
result.name: Jumbo Floating Restaurant

reviews.text:
To avoid the peak hour, you can enjoy the yum cha after 2pm.

There are 2 piers in Aberdeen to take the ferry to this restaurant, and this is totally free! So make use of it to enjoy the sea breeze in Aberdeen, and thank me later!

Loved it! Unique destination dining. You take a free boat ride across the marina to this massive floating restaurant. It's quintessentially an oriental artistic and architectural masterpiece. Opulent, vibrant and absolutely huge! The food is fabulous.

Definitely a memory making dining experience!

Very good experience. Just have transportation arrangements. Almost stranded unable to find taxi back to hotel. Food was delicious. Crispy spring roll, dim sum sample, BBQ pork bun, and best shrimp fried rice I have ever had. Also dessert served was like mango custard like mango flan.

Very ambient and authentic restaurant, surprisingly reasonable for the setting and delicious food served here. Very spacious and we'll decorated restaurant, staff is very professional and friendly..would highly recommend the crispy sweet and sour pork with pineapple and the prawn and scallops fried rice.. A must try if you visit Hong Kong

I was looking forward to eating here as I'd heard all about it. 'Don't believe the hype' it wasn't all that, trying to order was difficult as not many people spoke English, also we were charged for things we thought were included. Boat ride to restaurant was OK

result.name: 珍寶海鮮舫

reviews.text: 提供免費泊車優惠👍🏻👍🏻
味道不錯😊
水煮龍斑魚辣辣的很好吃👍🏻
점보 식당이 보이는 곳과 반대로 가면 무료 셔틀 상선 탈 수 있습니다. 맛은 숙소 앞에서 2틀 먹을 수 있는 돈으로 이걸?이란 느낌이에요.

선착장에서 무료로 페리가 왕복하면서 이동시켜 준다. 여행사를 통해서 간거라서 가격은 잘 모르고 코스로 나왔다. 기다림 없이 바로 들어가고 앉으니 음식도 바로바로 나오는데 전체적으로 맛은 괜찮았다. 
그리고 2층 홀 맨 앞에는 황제가 앉을 법한 곳에 의상도 빌려주고 사진찍기 좋은 곳도 있었다.
